Configure Git (if you haven't already):

    git config --global user.name "Your Name"
    git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"

Repository Initialization & Cloning

    Initialize a new Git repository:

git init

Clone an existing repository:

    git clone <repository_url>

Staging and Committing Changes

    Check the status of the repository:

git status

Add files to the staging area:

    Add a specific file:

git add <file_name>

Add all files:

    git add .

Commit changes:

    git commit -m "Commit message"

Working with Branches

    List all branches:

git branch

Create a new branch:

git branch <branch_name>

Switch to a different branch:

git checkout <branch_name>

Create and switch to a new branch in one command:

git checkout -b <branch_name>

Merge a branch into the current branch:

git merge <branch_name>

Delete a branch (locally):

    git branch -d <branch_name>

Working with Remotes

    Add a remote repository:

git remote add origin <repository_url>

View remotes:

git remote -v

Push changes to a remote repository:

git push origin <branch_name>

Pull changes from a remote repository:

git pull origin <branch_name>

Fetch changes without merging:

    git fetch

Undoing Changes

    Undo changes in a file (before committing):

git checkout -- <file_name>

Remove a file from the staging area:

git reset <file_name>

Reset to a previous commit (soft, mixed, or hard):

    Soft (keeps changes in the working directory):

git reset --soft <commit_id>

Mixed (keeps changes but unstages them):

git reset --mixed <commit_id>

Hard (discards changes):

git reset --hard <commit_id>
